Our skin is made mostly of collagen which provides a foundation for health & thickness to the skin. People under 30 have lots collagen which makes skin smooth & tight, but as we age we have less collagen which makes skin thinner, leading to more wrinkles.  Using peptides in skincare products sends a "message" to your skin that it has lost collagen & needs to generate more. This increase in collagen  plumps fine lines, boosts  thickness & gives your skin a more youthful appearance. "Keep smiling because life is a beautiful thing and there's so much to smile about." -Marilyn Monroe --- Happy Wednesday, friends! I am smiling today because I've survived a year in braces! 😁It's been quite a journey, and I sure miss eating Sour Patch Kids and Peachy Os, and being able to bite into things like a normal person. But for most of my life, my teeth have been the source of one of my biggest insecurities and fears (because I'm also a wimp when it comes to anything dental related, and avoided the dentist for an embarrassingly long time), so this has been a big step forward for me. Doing this in my 30s makes me feel like such a dork sometimes, and they make me look like I'm 16 - but hey, people finally started carding me again! 😆 Also, they sure hurt (still in pain from an appointment from 2 days ago), and brushing something like 5 times a day gets real annoying, real fast (especially while traveling). But I've never smiled so much in my life as I have in the last year, and after hiding my smile for so long, that feels SO good. (Oh, and PSA: you should definitely listen when your dentist tells you to floss, kiddos. Sharing the #love today on #wearestemsquad. This amazing man was my cheerleader on Sunday when I ran the SF @runrocknroll half marathon to raise money for the Parkinson's Disease Foundation. He surprised me with these awesome signs 8 miles into my run just after I crossed the Golden Gate Bridge. The timing couldn't have been more perfect and apparently the signs were effective because I ran the second half of the race faster than the first! . I've really enjoyed reading other #stemsquad posts today about love and how it's essential for getting through grad school, a challenging career or just life in general. I pride myself in being a strong, independent woman, but I also am proud that I can lean on people that I love when I need support or comfort. No matter how stressful life can get, or how many things go wrong even when this was your year to have things go right, remember you have your people who care for you and will help you get back on top. . Make sure to share the ❤today! 😘

Канатные трамваи (англ. Cable car) – это ещё один символ Сан-Франциско, который просто нельзя пропустить. Необыкновенно красивые старинные вагоны привлекают туристов своим внешним видом. Эти же трамвайчики вы встретите повсюду в сувенирных лавках в виде магнитов, шоколадок, декоративных фигурок, изображений, нанесённых на футболки, в общем, вы не пропустите их, приехав в Сан-Франциско. А на фотографии просто красивая открытка с изображением этого трамвайчика, бросившаяся мне в глаза в сувенирной лавке.  Пожалуй, надо отправить кому-нибудь такой пламенный привет! As a professional hairstylist, you sometimes just have to tell a client that it can't be done. As a professional hairstylist, you always have to take care of the client and their hair. 🖤 Client used a color remover with 20 volume developer as she was thinking of going blonde again. The color remover didn't strip everything out and the left picture is what she had when we started. She had bleached her hair numerous times and colored with different shades of blue, purple, and pink multiple times. After our consultation, we decided bleaching was not an option as her hair was too damaged and wanted to try and keep the integrity of her hair. We attempted different stand tests with different color variations. The right picture is to show the "muddiness" that stylists talk about. In the end, we ended up having to take her back to a rich red purple blend. 💜❤Client left happy and on her way to healthy hair! Eventually she will be blonde but it's going to take time, patience, and a good hairstylist. 😉

🌸✌🏻50 YEARS AGO ✌🏽🌼 In 2006 a 4 part documentary called "The Drug Years" aired on VH1. It was a series focusing on the birth and growth of the drug culture in The United States. The very first episode was focused on 1967 and #TheSummerOfLove in #SanFrancisco. Besides watching 'Full House' and 'Sister Act II,' this was my first real "exposure" to the city. I was captivated by the culture, the music, and the history. I was greatly impacted by the series and have thought about it ever since. It's been exactly 50 years since nearly 100,000 young people (hippies) converged in San Francisco's neighborhood Haight-Ashbury. I find it interesting that this is the year.. No! The SUMMER.. that I am moving to San Francisco!

|| I believe the universe always gives back more, no matter what you put into it, always more. I've noticed in my life that because I constantly reach out and actively seek opportunities, I receive a shower of opportunities in return. They may not happen right away, sometimes even years later, but when they do come, they arrive in the form of a big, exciting leap forward. It's important to remember that this phenomenon doesn't work unless you do; you'll get nothing if you do nothing. But if you keep pushing and using a shotgun approach to create any and every route for forward progression that you can think of, you will see that things happen, more than you expect, maybe even more than you deserve. I firmly believe life is supposed to be a positive experience. It's supposed to be great. But you will only get what you create. So make it a good one! ||

Lemon 🍋 garlic salmon 🐟 because fatty fish gives me liiiife!!! Recipe below ⬇️⬇️⬇️ - - 1. Arrange salmon like so (I got these babies at Cash & Carry cuz mama's a bargainer like dat 💰 - 2. Rub a tbsp of minced garlic evenly over all of them so they don't get jealous of one another - 3. Pour a squirt of lemon juice over them, I didn't measure I just grabbed this Costco bottle and hoped for the best lol - 3. Sprinkle dat S&P like "salt bae" 😎 - 4. Find some random crumbs of paprika you were saving for a moment like this, they were at the bottom of the bag of smoked paprika pecans you bought a week ago and you were like "hmm 🤔 this could make good seasoning..." and continue with yo salt bae-ness - 5. Realize you had 2 step 3's 😅 - 6. Seal it over with another foil cover and bake at 375deg x15mins - 7. Uncover the foil (be careful of the steam unless you're trying to do a spa-cleansing steam straight to da face 🙃) and broil another 2-3mins - 8. Eat like you give A FCK!!!! 🤗🍽

Сан-Франциско... Я влюбилась а этот город сразу, ну вот сразу, мгновенно,  как только увидела его очертания с моста, соединяющего Окленд и Сан-Франциско. Я не видела всех городов Соединённых Штатов, но однозначно, проехав Флориду, Калифорнию, Неваду, Аризону и Юту, могу сказать, что это самый красивый город в Америке, который я видела. Я пыталась два дня понять почему именно он. Ну, правда, что в нем казалось бы особенного? Такой же даунтаун, как во всех крупных городах Америки, хватает "треша", как во всех крупных городах Америки, много бездомных, много мигрантов, вроде всё как во всех других крупных городах, но нет... Сан-Франциско другой, пожалуй, он первый попавшийся мне американский город, у которого есть своё лицо. Для меня типичный американский крупный город - это бездушные небоскрёбы из стекла и бетона, миллион машин, яркая реклама, типичная малоэтажная застройка, "полный ноль" истории, "полный ноль" души и "полный ноль" неповторимого образа, не вызывающий ничего, кроме скучающего равнодушия или откровенного разочарования. Но Сан-Франциско вызвал эмоции, чего я точно не ожидала. Скажу больше, я действительно влюбилась в этот город. Наверное, уже ради этого стоило сюда прилететь. Я ждала, что понравится Лос Анджелес, по которому сходят с ума миллионы или Лас-Вегас, но это одни из самых больших разочарований, причём если к разочарованию от Вегаса я была внутренне готова, то вот Лос Анджелес для меня оказался самым неприятным городом в Америке, в который я решила вернуться только в аэропорт для сдачи арендованной машины и отлёта домой.  Но Сан-Франциско, правда, стоит того, чтобы его посетить и даже вернуться в него... Из Сан-Франциско с любовью ❤️! San Francisco, California, USA 🇺🇸.

By combining a symbol of virginity with her pregnant belly, we get a bizarre message about the babies being conceived without sexual relations – not unlike the Virgin Mary.  Beyoncé’s Grammy performance went even deeper into Virgin Mary symbolism while emphasizing the concept of immaculate conception.  At the beginning of the performance, Beyoncé stood stoically, as if in a religious painting, holding her belly while a divine glow was shining on her. Not unlike in her video album Lemonade, Beyoncé’s look is greatly inspired by the goddess Oshun. There are however added elements. Around her head are two ancient spiritual symbols: a halo and solar rays. These are often found on classic depictions of the Virgin Mary.  The seven solar rays around Beyoncé’s head gave her performance an even deeper esoteric meaning – one that refers to occult mysteries.(Apollo , Mithras and the Statue of Liberty)  During her visually-intense performance, Beyoncé was surrounded by loyal followers who revered the grounds she walked on. At one point, things got weird. **Beyoncé’s chair tipped very heavily backward – a maneuver that is NOT RECOMMENDED for pregnant women.(Image Above) .  Despite being a human goddess, Beyoncé is nevertheless submitted to the will of the industry that controls her. That chair represents the industry that could easily hurt her and her children. The same concept – a goddess controlled by dark forces – is at the core of her video- album Lemonade. Неожиданно ответ на вопрос “куда поехать” сам нашелся: родители собрались на Хевиз и предложили примазаться, что очень актуально. Будем мужу и папе лечить нервишки и валяться в грязях.  И поскольку любимый и прекрасный лоукост Wizzair предлагает билетики в Будапешт по 270 евро/чел на нужные нам даты (wat??), решили попробовать поехать на машине🚘🛣. Что особенно удобно, учитывая, что двое из нас аэрофобы, а муж параноик обмороков). . Но что же с визой? Я было почти впала в шоковое от радости состояние - выяснилось, что подаваться в других городах таки можно (но только в Одессе, Харькове и Днепре). Но ненадолго, ибо ближайшая доступная дата три дня назад была 19 апреля (в Одессе. ОДНА). На мое нытье “А что же нам делать, а впишите меня хоть куда-то, ну пожалуйста” сотрудник ВЦ обрадовал, что теперь у них работает услуга “любой каприз за ваши деньги” - Premium Lounge с записью на любой день, да еще и с чайком, бесплатными фотками, ксерокопированием и даже заполнением анкеты. Стоимость этого удовольствия - 75 евро, но я уже высчитала, что если ехать в Одессу даже на день и заказывать услуги курьера, фоткаться, ксерокопировать, получится не намного дешевле. Так что скоро затестируем этот их премиум. И заодно проверим, дадут ли мне нормальную мультивизу, наконец.  Ну а завтра едем в Буковель, буду обкатывать новую снарягу, которая дожидалась своего часа долгие месяцы, а заодно расскажу, как уже 8 год подряд мы дешево катаемся на самом элитном украинском горнолыжном курорте🏂. #ваутрип #wowtrip

Chinatown в Сан-Франциско это не просто район: это целый город 🎎! Здесь соответсвующие запахи, повсюду китайская речь (здешние жители даже не пытаются учить английский, им и так нормально😂👌🏻) , азиатская еда🍣🍱 и магазины, вывески на китайском и  везде развешаны красные фонарики 🏮это нереально фотогеничный район⛩!! Половину памяти в телефоне я забила им! Поэтому, если вы фанат Азии или наоборот не были в Азии, но хотите побывать: смело идите сюда! Таких аутентичных мест, ещё надо поискать! 🇨🇳 Пс. Когда смотрела фильмы и видела, что есть такие районы, всегда хотела вживую увидеть, что это такое! И вот сбылось ✔️ Ппс. Обратите внимание на фонари в этом районе! Все продуманно!! #china

Mind the little things. . When we think about saucha, or cleanliness, we might experience a small moment of panic when we realize that we have a mountain of things that need to be cleaned. We have to maintain a certain level of cleanliness in our homes, our work spaces, our bodies, and our minds. The sheer number of tasks necessary to keep everything neat and orderly can be overwhelming. . If, instead of doing massive overhauls or cleaning marathons, we took care of tasks one by one as they arose, I imagine we'd save a lot of time and energy. It's much easier and more rewarding to clean one little mess, than to be faced with a giant mess, or a big pile of little messes. . Mind the little things. Clean up messes as they arise. Wash dishes after each meal so you don't end up with a sink full of dirty dishes at the end of the week. Make healthy food choices regularly, and you likely won't feel the need to do month-long cleanse. Take the clearest expression of a yoga posture that you can, even if that means doing a level one or two of the pose. . Mind the little things.

На фото бабушка с внуком! Прочла в интернете и захотелось поделиться! Сочинение третьеклассницы на тему "Кто такая бабушка?" "Бабушка - это такая женщина, у которой нет своих детей. Она любит маленьких девочек и мальчиков, которые дети других людей. Дедушка - это тоже бабушка, только мужчина.Он ходит гулять с мальчиками, и они разговаривают о рыбалке и других вещах. Бабушкам ничего не надо делать, только приходить в гости. Они старые, и поэтому им нельзя бегать и много прыгать. Но они могут отвести нас на ярмарку, и у них должно быть много денег, чтобы покатать нас на карусели.Если они с нами гуляют, то они останавливаются, чтобы посмотреть на всякие вещи, например, на красивые листья или на гусениц. Они никогда не говорят: "Пошли быстрее".Они носят очки и могут вынимать свои зубы. Бабушки не должны быть очень умными, только отвечать на такие вопросы, как "Почему собаки гоняют кошек?" или "Где у червяка голова ?".Когда они читают нам книжки, они ничего не пропускают и не говорят, что эту сказку мы уже читали. Каждый должен стараться, чтобы у него была бабушка, потому что они единственные взрослые, у которых есть СВОБОДНОЕ  ВРЕМЯ ДЛЯ ДЕТЕЙ. #бабушка #бабушкавнук #моямама #мойсын #grandma #twinpeaks #sanfrancisco

I love restaurants that have seasonal menus. Ingredients picked fresh and from local farmers. @delarosasf does just that. This english pea bruschetta and the sunshine today reminded me that spring is here and all the amazing foods I love are coming into season. They shell their peas in house and mix with fresh mint and parmesan over sourdough bread. I mean what could be better? Oh yeah, their pizza that is made with artisan burrata mozzarella cheese. So maybe that 🙃 The name of my practice is Balance by Molly. I chose this name based on the concept of finding a balance in your food choices. Of listening to your body and what it is asking you for. Of knowing that bread and cheese one day (unprocessed and good ingredients of course 😉) and green smoothies and hippie buddha bowls the next is normal. I teach my clients how to put a stop to the food guilt and shame of treating yourself to what your body wants. Eat more food. Eat better food. Balance is 🗝. We are all only human. 💖✨

SAMAROLI LEDAIG 1997 45%  Island single malt scotch whisky  Distilled in 1997 from LEDAIG distillery  Bottled in Scotland in 2016 Selected cask n°800059 45% vol. (Notes de dégustation écrites sur l'instant, dans des conditions "bar" qui ne sont pas toujours propices à cet exercice.) Nez : crustacés à fond les ballons ! Ça sent vraiment l'océan. Ça s'ouvre sur des fruits à coques (amande), du cassis et des groseilles. Arrivent quelques épices douces et du poivre noir. Rappelle un genre de kilchoman mais plus robuste et plus mâture. Après une quinzaine de minutes d'aération dans le verre : sucre brun liquide et poivrons verts.  Bouche : Au départ assez aqueux et semble manquer de corpulence. Très épicé !  À la deuxième lampée, je garde le liquide en bouche une bonne vingtaine de secondes et la magie opère... La texture devient de plus en plus grasse, de la pêche bien juteuse apparaît. L'alcool est superbement intégré et on sent quasi pas les watts d'alcool. La tourbe est moins présente qu'au nez mais bel et bien là en fond. Le poivre et les épices sont définitivement présents.  Une belle finale sur du tabac, du bois, de la tourbe et de l'huile. C'est gras !  C'est un pur whisky de dégustation avec toute sa complexité. La texture en bouche est vraiment évolutive. On y retrouve la tourbe des Islay avec un supplément épices. C'est vraiment de la bonne came.  Verre vide : fruits secs (abricots), mangue au paprika séchée. #samaroli #ledaig #singlemalt #scotchwhisky #whisky #islay #peat #sanfrancisco #nihonwhiskylounge #passionboisson #sipimenté

Foster Care! Greetings, my name is Louie, but my foster parents call me “Louie the Lionhearted”. I may be small (only 6 pounds) but I have a huge personality. I’m a 2 year old neutered male Chihuahua. I’m housetrained and do great with dogs of all different sizes. I wasn’t sure about cats at first, but I live with cats in my foster home, so I could probably live with a dog-savvy cat or two. I like to burrow under blankets at night to keep warm. My ideal owner would be an adult-only home (sorry, no kids) with someone who has experience owning small dogs before. Since I’m in foster care I’m not at the shelter, but you can learn more about me or set up a meeting by contacting amarinakis@phs-spca.org or 650-340-7022 ext 374. At the wonderful #manresa in #sanfrancisco #losgatos  chef @davidkinch is cooking up a storm, I went for dinner after getting in the same day from London so the mind & body was on serious jet lag. The head was thinking it was breakfast time but the tummy knew otherwise. Some great inventive dishes coming out of his kitchen. A red pepper pate de fruit, black olive Madeline. A breakfast granola crisp, soft leek with marinated scallop & roe, a beautiful soft cooked egg with parsley & a spiced maple bacon syrup. Caviar with smoked sour cream & baby sorrel leaves,  beautiful crab meat with a yuzo pannacotta was outstanding. Spotted prawn with asparagus cooked in its own juice & butter with a herb crumb. A lovely salad of wild & garden herbs & flowers. Abalone & sea urchin with soba noodles with a brown rice stock was also delicious .... more to follow

We got a few DMs asking about Molly's attack. If it was something along the lines of a dog park scuffle or a little dog dog charging her off leash, both seem to be common experiences dog owners are having that are causing their dogs to become reactive. Unfortunately Molly didn't get into a little scuffle. The dog aggressed and full on attacked her 😞 This is why we are so impressed with how far she has come, a point where she can trust and feel confident around other dogs again. Not too long ago her Mom actually walked her at a local 'Strut Your Mutt' event with over 500 dogs! The No Place Project: San Francisco, California 1877 - 2 of 4 - Intersection Where the Anti-Chinese Rioters Were Stopped  At least 500 of the men at The Sandlot marched toward Chinatown. The San Francisco police were able to get a large contingent of officers out in front of the crowd, and just outside of Chinatown, at the corner of California and Dupont Streets, the police formed a double line to block the way. The mob charged the police line, but the police pushed them back. The size and force of the police line successfully halted the attack, and within an hour the marchers began to disperse.  Another mob from The Sandlot tried to go around to the north end of Chinatown, but they found another police line waiting for them there. Thwarted with their attempts at violence, the crowd gave up for the evening and an uneasy calm settled in that night. #noplaceproject #americanhistory #immigration #racism #chineseexlusion #chineseamericans #violence #sanfrancisco #california www.noplaceproject.com

Sunrise Oyster Point, CA (Just posting some old photo). This was taken on sunrise.  We got there around 5 AM.  A very quiet boat neighborhood.  While the rest of the guys were busy figuring out where the sunrise would come out, I quietly sneaked away from them and browsed the area around (I was the only gal photographer and considered myself a beginner). I found the spot where I wanted to shoot.  I was quiet and didn't want to wake up the people in the area.  But right after I was ready to shoot, the next thing I heard was the guys were approaching my area, noisily... (oh brother). Anyway, they were busily giving and exchanging camera settings.  I just kept my mouth shut and tried to keep the mosquitoes or bugs away from me.  And just recording the sunrise.  At the end, I was exhausted.  Shooting sunrise is always a payoff.  Getting up early, getting nice sunrise shots and always come back home tired.  But I love it 😍  #OysterPoint #California #BayArea #SanFrancisco #Sunrise #Boats #LongExposure

As we go about dropping random pins on conventional maps into this city we call home and explore uncharted corners bearing our tourist hats time and again, we can't help but gape at the wonder that is San Francisco! Full of color, full of culture, full of gastronomic wonders, full of musically driven audiences and artists alike, full of art, full of energy; and full of hustle and bustle! There's a beat to this city that simply refuses to be captured in mere words or two dimensional frames! Free spirits walk by the dozens here, carefree and jovial in their gaits, curious tourists appear like bubbly froth on freshly brewed beer and locals seem to never get over the wholesomeness of this concrete, artsy and strategically located jungle! The original hipster town remains our favorite home ground and we could hardly put into words at how thankful we are for it!! Now that's a corner of the city that I've never seen before! Have you? P.S. They have the most interesting and eclectic collection of vintage-y items in a dainty old thrift store right outside the alley!!! Made our day!!! And I'm glad we made a day out of this micro adventure!! Say what's up weird-camelback-rider-with no shoes on? Climate change is real. It is happening NOW. Carbon pollution is warming our planet and creating extreme droughts, flooding, wildfires and superstorms. Right now we are on track to see global temperatures rise up to 4 degrees by the end of the century. With a shift to clean energy we can still create a sustainable future, but we have to act now! Nature doesn't need people, people need nature. Our food, our water, our health, our jobs-they all rely on the health of the planet's ecosystems. But we are taking more from nature than nature can give. We are weakening the Earth's ability to provide the clean air, fresh water and food we depend on. We are creating a crisis! But we can end this crisis! I have teamed up with Conservation International to raise donations to support their organization by fundraising for the San Francisco Marathon I will be running in July. Conservation International is an amazing organization which works at every level, from remote villages to the offices of presidents and CEOs. Their work is moving entire societies towards a healthier, more sustainable path, so that we don't use up today what we are going to need tomorrow. Conservation International builds upon the foundation of science, field work and are finding global solutions to global problems. They have 3 elements: protecting our natural wealth, fostering effective governance and promoting sustainable production. Their vision is a healthy, prosperous world for the long term benefit of all people and life on Earth. I am proud to support such an inspiring organization! So please stand with me! Together we can make a difference to help save our planet. My fundraising page link is in my bio so please take a moment to donate. Археологический памятник на месте бывшего детинца и окольного города. Было окружено земляным валом, по кромке которого шел деревянный «паркан» (частокол), и рвом. Фрагмент вала сохранился в начале улицы Максима Горького (бывшей Замковой). В культурном слое находятся деревянные венцы жилых и хозяйственных построек, многоярусные настилы улиц, дворовые подмостки. В 1997 г. в честь 900-летия Пинска в северо-западной части городища установлен похожий на часовню памятный знак. #pinskbypinsk #pinsk  #Brest #berlin #berlin🇩🇪 #sinfrancisco #sanfrancisco #Belarus ##belarus🇧🇾 #belarustrip #belarustrevl

Si se animan por una Pasta con Albóndigas para el almuerzo de hoy, acá les explico cómo prepararla. ¿Qué opinan?  Para que pueda ver sus platos, no duden en compartirme sus fotos usando #SoyCocinero👇  Ingredientes Albóndigas: 500 gr. de Carne molida ½ taza de Pan en migas o rallado 2 Huevos batidos ¼ taza de Queso Parmesano Cebolla picada Pimentón verde Perejil Sal Ajo en polvo Pimienta Negra Aceite de Oliva  Salsa: 340 gr. de Pasta de Tomate 455 gr. de Salsa de Tomate Cebolla picada en cubitos Pimentón picado en cubitos ¼ taza de Vino Rojo de cocina  ¼ taza de Agua 2 cdas. de Azúcar Queso Parmesano al gusto Ajo en polvo Sal Perejil Pimienta Negra  Preparación Albóndigas: -Vierte todos los ingredientes en un bowl y amasa hasta integrar bien. -Prepara las Albóndigas con un diámetro de 5 centímetros aproximadamente. -Calienta Aceite de Oliva en un sartén y añade las Albóndigas. -Cocina hasta que doren de cada lado. -Retira del fuego y reserva.  Salsa: -Sofríe la Cebolla y el Pimentón en un chorrito de Aceite hasta que doren. -Luego, agrega la Salsa y Pasta de Tomate. Cocina a fuego lento durante 3 minutos aproximadamente. -Añade el resto de los ingredientes menos el Perejil y el Queso Parmesano. -Cocina a fuego lento hasta que tome consistencia. -Unos minutos antes de apagar, agrega el Perejil y el Queso. -Sirve calientes junto a tu Pasta y disfruta. 📷: @cheatdayeats

A dica é escolher lenços que conversem com as outras peças da mala! Vale ousar nas combinações de cores mix de estampas! A foto foi tirada há 3 anos e continua super atual! Misturei estampas e texturas com listras, poás e jacquard... Aliás, essa calça está há um bom tempo sem uso! Uma boa pela para os resgates de outono. A blusa, o lenço e a bolsa continuam em alta no armário revolto, são peças clássicas e atemporais! #sanfrancisco #california #mixdeestampas #blackandwhite #preparando #heightashbury #cool #armariosfechados #garimpeseuarmario  #resgatesrevoltos #grafite #streetart

All electric airplane called the Extra 330LE sets a new record speed of 210 mph (337.5 km/h) for electric aircraft. . The trial happened at the Dinslaken Schwarze Heide airfield in Germany on March 23, 2017. . The aircraft was equipped with a 260 kW motor from Siemens, that only weighed 50 lbs (110 kg). . The electric plane flew a distance of 1.9 miles (3 km) and then towed a type LS8-neo glider into the sky to a height of 1,968 ft (600 meters). . Back in its early 2000s heyday, That’s So Raven enjoyed a favorable four-year run, setting ratings records with its January 2003 premiere and continuing strong until its 2007 finale. Now, Disney has officially given a spinoff a green light. The multi-cam series, titled Raven’s Home, will pick up with Raven and Chelsea, who find themselves as divorced single mothers raising their two separate families under one big roof.  The original Disney sitcom starred Raven-Symoné as the titular lead character, a psychic teen balancing friends, family, and her fashion design dreams in San Francisco. It also featured Orlando Brown and Anneliese van der Pol as Eddie and Chelsea, Raven’s best friends, and Kyle Massey as Cory, her younger brother. The new series will follow the first one closely, as one of Raven’s kids begins to show signs that they’ve inherited her psychic abilities, effectively flipping an already chaotic household upside down. ... While I'm annoyed at myself for not taking a better photo (so the fries look less washed out 🍟🍟 because they were delicious AF), I also could not wait to dig into this burger. My dad grew up going here and took me to this place when I went to college in the city. The restaurant is low-key and they grind their own meat for their burger patties. Plus they have these banana milkshakes that are pretty fan-freaking-tastic. I usually get the Don's Burger, cooked medium, which is what is pictured here since I am a sucker for mushrooms. If you're around inner Richmond and want a solid burger, I highly recommend. And I could be more mature. I practice driving and learn English whole time in here. And I got lots of friends who are came from different countries. Chisa is from japan, Kevin is from Vietnam ,EdRado is from New Zealand, Giovany is from Brazil, Krissa is from Taiwan and Tammy is from China. So I could be more International.  If I do my best in the class maybe I could go in the master class Sunday actually I felt that memorize the vocabulary is the most important thing to master English. . . #在机场滯留第十二个小时的我 一次非常不顺利的旅行 运气背得想起来笑得不能自已 接二连三的故障 行程一再改变直至取消 去看闺蜜的路程充满着未知 也莫名来了个一个人睡机场的经历 累得过了头 时差也还是没调好 一宿基本没合眼 凌晨三点的机场很安静 店铺都关门了 排在United customer desk的队伍依旧很长 时常传来鬼佬的爆粗 也有人再counter发牢骚大哭 环顾四周 都是并排的情侣 或是三三两两结伴的朋友 肚子忽然尴尬叫了一声 在异常寂静的空气里显得突兀  昏睡了几分钟又冷醒 看到一个老爷爷在旁边玩游戏 好可爱 心情突然也没那么差了 其实真的是倒霉到妈妈又开始叫我回家 记得好朋友曾经跟我说陈佩欣你怎么那么容易发生那么事情 我在反省是不是我安排时候出了什么差错 但好像大部分都是与天气有关 我已经尽力避免不确定事件的发生 我尽可能拥有了一个周详的计划  以前我害怕别人喜欢指指点点说一个女生跑来跑去干嘛 其实很简单 我想趁我工作前有精力有时间去看看我的老朋友 跨越一个海去看我的好闺蜜  我能做的做到了 起码我坐了一趟像过山车的飞机 旁边的人吓哭了我还是很淡定 睡了一晚机场思考了一下小人生 也尽力投诉了弄丢我行李的英航 见到了想见的人 知道了许多更应该早点知道的故事  我觉得我很帅气 因为我又成长了一点 没什么好抱怨的 这都是我人生的一个经历而已  我不是不需要人陪 只是在没有人陪的时候 我一个人也可以  谢小玉我要飞多两程飞机去见你 是不是要感动哭 #sanfrancisco #Airport #Delayed #cancelledflight #sleepover

By @richardescalona - ¿Qué necesita el Mundo hoy?  ___  Escúchalo y siente su dolor. Oración para pedir por la Paz:  Señor, haz de mi un instrumento de tu paz. Que allá donde hay odio, yo ponga el amor.  Que allá donde hay ofensa, yo ponga el perdón.  Que allá donde hay discordia, yo ponga la unión.  Que allá donde hay error, yo ponga la verdad.  Que allá donde hay duda, yo ponga la Fe.  Que allá donde desesperación, yo ponga la esperanza.  Que allá donde hay tinieblas, yo ponga la luz.  Que allá donde hay tristeza, yo ponga la alegría.  Oh Señor, que yo no busque tanto ser consolado, cuanto consolar,  ser comprendido, cuanto comprender,  ser amado, cuanto amar.  Porque es dándose como se recibe,  es olvidándose de sí mismo como uno se encuentra a sí mismo,  es perdonando, como se es perdonado,  es muriendo como se resucita a la vida eterna. They hold many small businesses that might not have been able to start on a main street but can thrive just a bit out of the way. Australians mix indoor and outdoor space with aplomb.  This "laneway" is actually an alley in San Francisco, but it reminded me of Sydney. I walked down it thinking of ibises and rainbow lorikeets. Lee Mingwei (American, born 1964) 100 Days with Lily, 1996 Five chromogenic prints . . "Taiwan-born artist Lee Mingwei stages rarely considered rituals of daily life as participatory activities in museums and public spaces, treating them almost as sacred practices. In this way, he encourages audiences to revalue them and the interactions they foster. In 1995 Lee planted a lily in a pot and carried it with him wherever he went for 100 days as the plant sprouted, grew, bloomed and died. A private contemplative activity, his action was also a catalyst for unplanned social exchanges, many inevitably focused on such profound issues as love, worship, loss and mourning. The documentary images from Lee's life with the plant in San Francisco are overprinted with excerpts from the journal he kept durning the project." . #LeeMingwei #100DaysWithLily #1996 #chromogenicprint #chromogenic #barnesfoundation #personofthecrowd #philly #philadelphia #lily #lilies #ritual #activity #sacredpractice #sacred #interaction #100days #sprout #grow #bloom #die #journal #contemplative #socialexchange #love #worship #loss #mourning #SanFrancisco

Hola #pandiamigos! Hoy quiero compartirles dos publicaciones sobre mis inteligentes hermanos primates 🐒 La primera es sobre #Koko, una de mis hermanitas #gorilas más famosas a nivel mundial pues puede comunicarse mediante señas 👍🐼 Nació el 4 de julio de 1971 en #SanFrancisco, #California, y fue adiestrada por mi pandiamiga doctora Francine Patterson y otros científicos de la Universidad de Stanford 🐾 Sabe más de 1000 signos basados en la Lengua de Señas Americana (en inglés, American Sign Language, ASL, usado por mis pandiamigos humanos con discapacidad auditiva o mudez) y también comprende aproximadamente 2000 palabras de inglés hablado 🐼🎉 ¡Miren el trabajo tan espectacular que lograron! 💖 Aunque hay científicos que opinan que sólo copia y no entiende realmente... Pero yo creo que es muy inteligente y si entiende todo 💡 Ella tiene un mensaje que darles a todos, les recomiendo que vean las dos partes del vídeo (gracias a @laluciernaga_09 por recordarme este vídeo de mi hermanita) 🐼💋 Una #curiosidad que supe gracias a mis amigos de @wikipedia es que Koko es diminutivo de Hanabi-Ko, que significa "Hija de los fuegos artificiales" en japonés, en referencia al día de su nacimiento (Día de la Independencia de los #EstadosUnidos) 🐼💚🇺🇸 Aunque el traductor de mis amigos de @Google me mostró algo un poquito diferente jeje 🎆🎆🎆 Sígueme y creemos una linda comunidad de pandas 🐼💚 🎍🎋🎍🎋🎍🎋🎍🎋 #DesarrolloSocial #Desarrollosustentable #DesarrolloSostenible #sostenibilidad #Conciencia #Consciencia #LaNaturalezaNosObserva #Naturaleza #Gorila #Motica #Comunidad

(1/2) "I wish I had some story about Sleepy to make him a larger than life hero. Instead, Sleepy was just like any other person out there. He was always able to make us laugh and was solid when shit hit the fan. Like all of us soldiers, he was terrified of what could happen, but faced it with bravery and a sense of humor. We all had hard times coming home, some of us were able to pull through others were not. I wish I could have done more to help him pull through, but there was only so much I could do. Now, I did the walk for honor, for Sleepy's honor, and for my own." Eric is an Afghanistan War Veteran who walked in the American Foundation for Suicide Prevention Overnight Walk in San Francisco 2016 raising money for mental health resources and breaking stigma against mental illness for his comrade, who died by suicide post deployment, and himself. -- @afspnational @afsporegon #candidphotography #candid #photojournalism #photojournalist #photojourney  #suicideprevention #afspovernight #nikonphotography #nikon #veteran #ptsd #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #stigma #stigmafree #raiseawareness #portraitphotography #portrait #portlandphotographer #portlandoregonphotographer #pdxphotographer #pnwphotographer #sanfrancisco  #rip #inmemory

This week's #SuccessSaturday goes out to @lizlemonsf. She came in after a friend recommended she join. Liz was hesitant at first, as she was nervous about a prior back injury and group training. But Liz decided to give it a try and came in 3-4 days per week with great energy and willingness to try. It's been 2.5 months and with our 1-on-1 training in a group setting Liz is moving better, feeling better, and absolutely crushing it. When she joined modified push-ups from her knees were a struggle but today she did sets of 5x full, strict chest-to-floor push-ups. Focus on the process, the results will come. Proud of you Liz! 페리에 내려서 자전거 반납하러 가는 길. 이곳에 보딘 본점이 있다....들어가 기념품만 샀다. 예쁜 바게트 마그넷과 예림이 선물. 바로 옆 피셔맨즈와프는, 수산시장처럼 쭈르륵 마켓이 형성되어 있고 게를 쪄서 팔거나 대부분 해산물을 판다. 난 해산물을 썩 안좋아하는 관계로 멀찍이서 대충 보고 떠났다. 보기만 해도 내가 먹는것처럼 속이 비렸다. 그래도 시장은 어떤 종류이던 구경하는 재미가 있다..! 자전거가 너무 즐거웠던지라, 여운이 남아 바로 반납하지 않고 피셔맨즈쪽도 자전거로 조금 돌아다녔는데 나중엔 더 타고 싶어도 엉덩이가 장조림 절이듯 물렁해지는 것처럼 아파서 반납했다. 직원언니랑 아저씨도 너무 친절한, 떠오르면 기분 좋은 가게..! 고마웠어요. #sanfrancisco #fishermanswharf #bicyclerentals

Light hitting water 💙 - - One of two cenotes at Dzitnup, about 7km west of Valladolid, Cenote Samulá is a lovely cavern pool with álamo roots stretching down many meters from the middle of the ceiling to drink from the source.  Pedaling a rented bicycle to the cenotes takes about 20 minutes. By bike from the town center take Calle 41A (Calzada de los Frailes), a street lined with colonial architecture. Go one block past the Templo de San Bernardino park and turn left on Calle 54, then make a right on Calle 49, which becomes Avenida de los Frailes and hits the old highway. Follow the ciclopista (bike path) paralleling the road to Mérida, then turn left at the sign for Dzitnup and continue for just under 2km; Samulá will be off this road to the right and Dzitnup a little further on the left. - - 📷: @everchanginghorizon - - We would love to invite you to join world's one of its kind travel social networking website for all you lovely and wonderful Trippyowls. I will remember yesterday forever. I walked so extensively that my heels bled. However, I smiled so much and my breath was taken away so often by this city that I didn't even notice the injuries until I took off my shoes later that evening. This is a city where nature was at the forefront, where dogs greeted me at little French restaurants, where jazz musicians filled the air of the streets with their sweet sounds, where everyone was smiling and turn after turn stunning vistas awaited my simple midwestern eyes. I am not naive. I know I could never afford to live there or even venture to dream that I could, but I was without a doubt love-drunk with this city. There is so much that I was unable to see on such a short stay, but I am confident that when I return I will be just as amazed. #sanfrancisco #thecity #sanfran #goldengatebridge #chrissyfield #fillmorestreet #fillmorestairs #corgi #bayarea #sanfranciscobay #sunset #champagnetasteonatapwaterbudget

LOVE THIS TOWN 💯 . Hayward is a bridge between two worlds. Nature and the city flow seamlessly here. In some places we're all urban bustle and grit; in others we're as serene as a sunset on the bay. We have our own style here, our own vision. There is no other place on earth that quite compares. . Now, as the sun awakens from its winter slumber and spreads new life across the land, we look out and see our home with new eyes. There, in the distance, we can see our future. The city at the crossroads. A city on the rise. Hayward, California. . #hayward . Image by @shadow.ofthe.lens: Footbridge and cityscape at Eden Landing Ecological Reserve, Hayward, Calif. . We are the original and still the best. Accept to imitations. Follow @haywardthrives . ✌️📷❤

A year ago I went on an adventure to California. It all started when one evening I heard the Lord say, "I want you to go to California." I had no money for this trip and no place to stay while on the West Coast but the Lord provided everything! When I look back on this adventure, I see the Lord's hand at work, I see where He was teaching me to trust Him more in the unknowns, and showing me that when I listen to His voice there are surprises and so many good things ahead even when it doesn’t make sense in the moment.  One of these surprises was the city of San Francisco! I had dreamed of coming to this city since I was 9 or 10 but didn't think it was going to happen till way later in my life, but it was as if the Lord had another plan. I'm thankful for this journey I am on and for the people I got to take this adventure with. • • • • #california #sanfrancisco #goldengatebridge #friends #adventure  #missions #travel #surprises

A Spanish shop in San Francisco's Mission district. The area is a hub for many of the city's Hispanic residents - some of whom are living in the US without legal status. San Francisco has declared itself to be a "sanctuary city", which means the city's cops are not allowed to hand over illegal immigrants to Federal authorities for deportation. President Trump has vowed to take away federal funding from cities that refuse to comply with federal immigration laws, and San Franciso stands to lose more than a billion dollars in funding. But the city remains defiant, with the mayor declaring: "We're ready, we have to fight." This is where I grew up almost 50% of the time. Grandma and Grandpa's house was just as much our home as it was theirs. We used to climb up that hill, which we called snake mountain, with pieces of cardboard and slide down as fast as we could. There used to be a big barn over by the peppercorn tree and my grandpa had a goat named Nanni who lived there. We were forbidden from going into it, but we did it anyway. Nanni wasn't always nice, so we carefully snuck in and ran out before we were head butted. When I turned 15, I learned to drive a stick shift on this land and later my grandpa taught me how to work on tractors...not that much of that sank in, haha. This is where I learned how to set the table, cook by taste, and bake with only the best German chocolate. This is my home. ❤️#home #homeiswheretheheartis

::Motivation Monday:: Striving for perfection may be the most soul crushing endeavor we undertake. Trying to control everything is a dead end as well. Authenticity and the right self acceptance are two huge keys to happiness. The things that keep us from moving forward are anchored in our past. Whoa, right?!? We should figure out what those things are, understand them, and then get rid of them. Fear is the biggest liar that we have and can manifest itself in a plethora of different ways; confusion, unhappiness, control, paranoia, overthinking, anxiousness, apprehension, etc. In fact sometimes because of those anchors that hold us back, fear can make something look like the wrong path when it's the exact one we need. • I'd like to encourage you to live in the moment while not letting the past affect your present and future. Don't try to control the situations going on in your life and don't try to control what path your life is taking. Do not let fear or anxiety take over your thought process. • #oceanbeach #sf #sanfrancisco #beach #fog #moodygram #motivationmonday #igerssf #bettertogether #communityovercompetition #dontdolifealone #speaklife #sfguide #sf_insta #wildbayarea #karlthefog #outsideculture #optoutside #meetthemoment #beoutdoors #theoutbound #headedelsewhere #wildernessculture #thehappynow #livethelittlethings #darlingmovement #getoutstayout #nothingisordinary #alphaleftcoast #exploretocreate

Since I was a kid, I loved art. I loved drawing and coloring in elementary and had quite the imagination. It followed me  through middle school and high school. I didn't start painting on Canvas until I was 23. I've never sold anything though... I always just did it for fun, I honestly never felt that anything I created would be "good enough" for someone to actually want to purchase. I've always thought there are better people, which is completely true, BUT What I've realized is that there isn't bad art. Every piece you'll see is someone's masterpiece and expression that was birthed from that beautiful heart and creative mind. I have gone YEARS being insecure with what I create. It's super annoying!! So this year I'm going to make art one of the things I'm just going to be confident in, because life is too short to waste it on holding yourself back due to the negative thoughts you feed yourself. These buildings looked well-kept and functional from a distance, but their dilapidation made for an eerie glance at Angel Island. Fort McDowell was built in the late 19th century and, among other purposes, was used as a detention station for Japanese, German, and Italian immigrant residents of Hawaii in WWII. I love being able to explore like this by sailboat - it opens up a whole world of discovery. And I cannot wait to teach about the body of wisdom tomorrow night on The Wild Calling. I dare you to do one thing today that your body deeply desires, to make space to listen to its messages, to begin to build a relationship to trusting it. I can't even put into words how special today was! I've wanted to cycle over the Golden Gate Bridge for as long as I can remember 🇺🇸❤. The weather was as perfect as it could have been and our life was made before we even got to the bridge; we ate avocado on sourdough (so Cali!) surrounded by 30 or so fluffy dogs playing on the beach. Sometimes you worry places you've seen in movies and on postcards will never live up to expectations, but this really did. It was incredible! NUESTRO SUEÑO  En el palpitante silencio de la noche,puedo oír tu melodioso susurro en la distancia, Me llamas,voy a ti y tomados de la mano volamos, Enredados de caricias y besos nos amamos. Entre nubes y arco iris de colores te respiro,viajamos por nuestros sueños de ilusiones como niños, soy viento,soy hombre,soy fantasía en campo de girasoles, Soy poema en tus brazos,soy verso,soy prosa. Eres mi secreto escondido,el sueño más querido, Eres amor,laberinto y deseos sin control. Eres ráfagas de pasión,en mi piel sin tregua, Eres caudal de emoción en mí torrentoso amor.  Mientras en el palpitante susurro del silencio,la noche contempla bajo ese manto lunar nuestro sueño,sin barreras ni distancias.... Tú, eres mi felicidad,mi sueño,mi esperanza anhelada que con lágrimas en el corazón espera con ansias el día pueda ver,sentir y tocar todo tu ser que en la distancia crece y vive un amor que se mantiene vivo bajo la luz de tu mirada. 🌻🍃🌹🍃 #goodmorning#love#poema#poesiaenletras#girasoles#onlyyou#prince#bohemianstyle#tuesday#loveislove#smile#romatic#photography#califormia#sanfrancisco#instapic#morningpost#follow#comment#niceshot#shooting#latinolover#mexican#spanish#jewish#beardedman

San Francisco / Bogotá ---------------------------------------------------- Este templo es una maravilla inesperada.  Esta justo en medio de la locura de la ciudad, se encuentra sobre la avenida principal, justo la que  cierran para hacer la vía recreactiva (esa que fue la original que inspiró a nuestra quería vía de  Guadalajara), a unas 5 cuadras antes de la plaza bolívar en donde se encuentra la Catedral.  Y justo está en donde esa avenida principal se junta con otra que maneja el tránsito del  Transmilenio (como del estilo del macrobus) por lo cual ahí suele haber mucho movimiento tanto  peatonal como automovilístico.  La fachada del templo es pequeña, fácilmente puede pasar desapercibido entre tanto movimiento  y entre tantos otros templos tan bonitos por la misma zona; yo mismo me sentí tentado a dejar  pasar la oportunidad de entrar, pero bueno, ya me estoy acostumbrando a que entrar a un templo  sea una cuestión casi obligada para mi emoción de viajero y no me lo iba a permitir.  Pasé por ahí tres días, los dos primeros estaba cerrado y el tercero había mucha fila para entrar,  eso me llamó aún más la atención sobre el templo, así que decidí ir a buscar otros y volver por la  tarde.  Cuando regresé seguía habiendo mucha gente afuera, pero ya no lo iba a posponer más, ya se me  estaba acabando el tiempo en Colombia y quién sabe cuándo volveré, así que me formé y esperé  mi turno de pasar sin entender el porqué de tanto interés en un templo ͞equis͟. ----------------------------------------------------- #elperiplodemanu #trabeliev #trabelievers #enmoviviendo #youcat #entendiendomife #catecismo  #viajes #travel #catholictravel #viajescatólicos #católico #viajerocatólico #peregrinando #pilgrim  #catholicism #church #catholicchurch #iglesia #templo #iglesiacatólica #Bogotá #colombia  #temploscolombia #jóvencatólico #youcatméxico #gopro #SanFrancisco

What is "Prana In vs. Prana Out" as referenced below in part 6 of my interview with @amalaprenatal?  Ask yourself these questions: What fuels you? What brings you joy? What gives you energy and life? What is your dharma, your purpose? What feeds you? The answers to these questions make up "Prana In" - that which gives you life.  Now ask yourself: what are the things that drain you, give you stress? What can you let go of? What can you say no to? What no longer serves you? The answers to these questions make up your "Prana Out" - that which takes away from your universal lifeforce. This week, how will you prioritize this balance of Prana In and Prana Out? #maintainbalance  #Repost @amalaprenatal with @repostapp ・・・ Part 6 of our interview with Shannon Terschluse @findyourprana ------------------------- Q: How has Amala’s Prenatal Yoga Training affected your teaching? A: Amala’s training has affected my teaching in so many positive ways! Training brought me back to the very basics of yoga after so many years of focusing on teaching asana and the physicality of the practice. I loved exploring Sankalpa and Vikalpa, the Koshas, and the idea of “Prana In vs. Prana Out” – all important ideas and theories that forced me to reflect on my own practice. I loved learning new meditations and feel grateful to be able to use so many of these meditations from training in my own teaching, both to pregnant women and non-pregnant people alike. Amala’s training allowed me to connect more deeply with my own yoga practice on mind, body, and spirit levels, which in turn, have helped me connect more deeply with students as a teacher.

Which is the tallest building?. Seen here from the corner of Pacific Avenue the Sentinel Building, a copper green flatiron style building completed in 1917 appears to stand as tall as the Transamerica Pyramid built in 1972. In fact it is only 8 stories high while the four sided pyramid has 48 floors and was the tallest building in San Francisco a few months ago. The façade has a coating of crushed quartz which gives it the light colour. Both buildings have changed ownership in recent years with the Sentinel Building now belonging to film-maker Francis Ford Coppola.

Primeiro jantar em #sanfrancisco foi delicioso, foi como um abraço depois de dois dias inteiros entre avião, aeroportos, trem e metrô. Na quadra seguinte ao hotel, no bairro Castro, ficamos tentadas a pegar um bistrô (lotadão) que faz a terça da ostra a 1 dólar, mas a gente queria algo mais quente e demos de cara com o Chow. Com frente modesta, pelo vidro vimos a casa cheia com todo tipo de gente e clientes comendo em bowls, entramos e plim! Que jantar delicioso! Tem de saladas lindas a massas com cara ótima, sanduíches e noodle! Dá pra escolher entre médio e grande - pedimos a porção média, bem ótima. O meu era apimentado, com gengibre, alho, frango e carne e muuuito coentro (❤❤❤), fatia de pão rústico. Saiu a 14,50 dólares. Acompanhei com taça de vinho da casa, a 13 dólares - caro, mas foi a primeira noite, né? Eu e @marilins pagamos uma conta de 57,55, com serviço incluso. O Chow fica na 215 Church Street, no Castro. Curti demais! Passa aa fotinhos pro lado pra ver mais 💁 #sanfrancisco #sãofrancisco

Chinatown in San Francisco ⛩ 📎Chinatown есть практически во всех крупных городах США, но Чайнатаун в Сан-Франциско является самым старым и зародился он в 1870 году. 📎Здесь находится самое обширное поселение китайцев вне пределов Азии - около 150000 человек, и развместились они всего в 24 кварталах города. И это всего лишь часть иммигрантов из Китая, так как остальная часть проживает в других района города. 📎Начало района находится на Bush Street, а самыми туристическими улицами являются Grant Avenue и California Street. Для аутентичности стоит пройтись по соседним улицам, где вы не услышите не единого английского слова. 📎Выбор сувениров здесь не особо хорош и отличается по цене, поэтому советую особо не надеяться на этот район. Нам Чайнатаун в Нью-Йорке и Вашингтоне понравились больше, так как там они кажутся более аутентичными, но посетить этот район стоит, особенно если прогуляться до него по Financial District. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . #sanfrancisco #chinatown #sf  #путешествиепоамерике #california #roadtrip #roadtripusa #architecture #путешествия #wanderlust #usa #usatrip #traveling #travelgram #travelphotography #instatravel #igmasters #bestintravel #ourplanetdaily #seetheworld #wonderful_places #beautifuldestinations #exklusive_shot #doyoutravel #инстаграмнедели #travelstoke #welltraveled  #travelingwithkat

📲@everart.io 🙌🏾CONGRATS @legacybros  Courtesy @ancestorproject  We are pleased to announce the recent appointment of Daniel Dunson as curator and ambassador of the Ancestor Project @ancestorproject. Dunson is the first African American to join the Osramba team; his goal is to link the project to our brothers and sisters of the diaspora. As head curator, Dunson will be curating exhibitions throughout Africa and the Western world, and will serve as the African American representative for the project. His curatorial debut with The Faux-Reedom Exhibition will take place in June (TBA) at Cape Coast Castle in Cape Coast, Ghana.  Dunson recently graduated from The University of Illinois at Chicago, where he studied art history. He is a 2016 Fulbright Grant recipient and Gilman Scholarship fellow. Dunson is forming a lifelong career in the fields of art history and visual culture. His research as an art historian has been primarily focused on figurative representations within Black Atlantic Art. Dunson has spent the last four years studying in West and North Africa analyzing tethers of the African Diaspora, while unifying them with contemporary and traditional African art. Dunson’s art criticisms, and editorials have been recently published in magazines in France and England, and he has presented his art historical research at symposiums and conferences in the United States, Morocco, South Africa, and Ghana. Dunson is currently conducting research that positions portraiture aligned with the art of space, place, and memory, and the Middle Passage as he surveys the visual culture of Ghanaian cemeteries and funerary arts. Dunson’s digital curatorial practice on Instagram (@legacybros) primarily focuses on figurative representations of blackness. Midori and Pablo were really my kind of couple! @Midori.Sour contacted me way back in early January, when I was a newbie to the US and seeking any kind of opportunity to shoot in this place where I knew no-one! I offered a special deal and Midori found me on MeetUp and immediately got in touch! From the moment we first spoke I knew that he had a special kind of vision for her shoot and I loved the locations she described. We met up about a month ago and brainstormed some ideas - this girl has a killer creative vision which I am super inspired by! Fast forward 2 and a half months from our first contact and we finally got to shoot her and Pablo's sun-drenched celebration of their engagement in Lands End, San Francisco. We had waited so long for the weather to be right, because Midori really wanted that backlit feel with the serene & beautiful Californian light... and this was something I was determined to give her. Unfortunately that was easier said than done with the winter we've just had (and has returned with a vengeance today, it seems). But we finally got our day towards the end of March and I'm delighted to be able to publish an image or two from Midori and Pablo's magical shoot. More to follow plus blog post. Congratulations, Midori & Pablo and what an honor it was to get to know you a little!

the Golden Gate Bridge — был самым большим висячим мостом в мире с момента открытия в 1937 году и до 1964 года.  Общая длина моста — 2737 м, длина основного пролёта — 1280 м, высота опор — 227 м над водой, масса — 894 500 т.  Высота проезжей части над поверхностью воды во время прилива составляет 67 м. ⋆⋆⋆⋆⋆⋆Day2 サンフランシスコを訪れるのは、２回目。 １回目は20年前の1997年、私が10歳の時でした。 母が昔留学していた時お世話になった ホストファミリーの妹さん(Jenny)の結婚式に参列する為、 まだ子供だった私と妹も一緒に 連れて行ってもらいました。 Jennyが私の名前でFacebookを探し当ててくれたおかげで10年前に繋がり、今回の再会に至りました。 この時ほど、Facebookをやってて良かったと思ったことはありません。 . 今回の渡米目的は私の友人の結婚式でしたが、 サンフランシスコなんてそうそう来られないという事で、20年ぶりにホストファミリーの皆んなに会いたい、 会わせたい！との想いで、今回母と一緒に渡米しました。 Jenny, Chris, Fred, Dianne。 温かく迎え入れてくれて本当に感謝しかないです。 . #instadaily#travel#trip#ca#california#sanfrancisco#sonoma#stockton#beautiful#memories#usa#america#サンフランシスコ#カリフォルニア#ストックトン#ホストファミリー#結婚式#旅#旅行#旅日記

Территория острова использовалась как защитный форт, позже как военная тюрьма, а затем как сверхзащищённая тюрьма для особо опасных преступников и тех, кто совершал попытки побега из предыдущих мест заключения. В настоящее время тюрьма расформирована, остров превращён в музей, куда ходит паром из Сан-Франциско от пирса номер 33. #Alcatraz #Алькатрас #СанФранциско  #Калифорния #California #SanFrancisco #четвёртыйпунктСанФранциско #всемдобра #ценитемгновения #счастьевмелочах #путешествиепоСША #travelling #США #USA

I would like to bring attention to a Sunset family who is an integral part of this village, giving much of their time and energy to helping to make our village a better place but are themselves struggling with an extreme "life challenge" and could really use our help... Charlie suffers from the genetic disease PKD (Polycystic Kidney Disease) and desperately needs a kidney donated to him. The process of donating a kidney is much easier than one might think and labor laws allow for time off to do so. I feel that somewhere in this village is someone who can help Charlie, a student teacher at AP Gianini who has an adorable little daughter named Alice and an amazing wife named Ashley @aesummers Who is super proactive in our community as the legislative aide to Supervisor Katy Tang. Both Charlie and Ashley grew up in the Outer Sunset... good chances you know them or have crossed paths. They need our help. Please consider donating a kidney or help to get the word out. More information at www.facebook.com/KidneyforCharlie or please feel free to reach out to me as I happy to give you more information and/or introduce you to them. I believe that somewhere in our Sunset village is the benevolent, kind soul who can help them. Please help me to connect Charlie and his beautiful family with a life saving kidney. #sunsetsf #outersunset #sf #sanfrancisco #kidney #kidney #pkd #polycystickidneydisease #community #kidneydonation #sunsetdistrict #sunsetlove

🌿🌿🌿Seven months ago today I was walking around Mission and saw this beautiful place - greenery was bursting with freshness, sundrops were jumping from leaf to leaf... It was not a park, or any outdoor space. Nor it was a greenhouse, or a flower shop... A venue with large windows and lots of plants - I wondered what it was: a cafe, a bar...? I walked inside. It turned out to be a hair salon. I was fascinated - and booked an appointment for the following day. My stylist was Jenny - a friendly petite beauty with long gorgeous red hair. I told her the story of my travels along the coast of California in search of a new hometown. San Francisco was my very first stop but thus far I was not quite impressed by it. And she told me how much she loved this city and its diversity... Seven months later here I am, back where I started. Same city, same hair salon and guess what - serendipitously, same Jenny @jennybeans 💇🏻

My first #Switchfoot show and VIP was three years ago today.  #FadingWest #RegencyBallroom #SanFrancisco #Stars #LoveAloneIsWorthTheFight #DarkHorses #YourLoveIsASong #CasualJon  Can't wait to catch a few shows #LookingForSummer  They actually came to UC Davis with Relient K in 2007 when i was a freshman living on campus. I didn't manage the courage to try to buy tickets until the discounted student ones had already sold out and i couldn't afford regular price. The night they performed, my dad picked me up to go home for the weekend. I was so sad as we passed by the ARC and saw their buses.  I left work early and took Amtrak and BART to get to San Francisco. I decided to do VIP since it was only $47 and i wanted to be up close for the general admission show. Google maps told me the venue was a mile away so I decided to walk instead of waiting for a bus. It didn't tell me that part of the mile included a mountain climb hahahah.  I didn't even know the guys names at that point. They introduced themselves but i was still all disheveled from the trek so i don't remember what i said to them.  I was already in bed by the time Jon tweeted that he was doing an aftershow and I wouldn't have made it back in time. The same thing nearly happened earlier  this year in Redding but i zipped back to the venue and caught an epic song and a half.

*TOP 10 HOLIDAYS - AMERICA* . Thought I would share my top 10 favourite holidays (in no order) in the world... next on the list is America. . America has got to be up there with the best..... . THE GOOD MOMENTS:  1️⃣ Diversity: from Miami to Vegas to LA to New York to Philly to San Fran to so many more places, I truly believe no two places I have been to are the same. From the accent to the culture to the sights to the architecture. 2️⃣ Shopping: omg, I don't think people in America realize how spoilt they are with the shopping in the states 3️⃣ People watching: I could sit all day and just watch life past me by in America. Of all the places I have visited in the world #Miami is in the top 3 places and I must say the people watching there is phenomenal. I just love it. . THE OTHER BITS NO ONE EVER TOLD ME 1️⃣ How addictive it is to want to keep traveling and see new parts of America 2️⃣ How I will need to diet every time I return from America. So much delish food 3️⃣ How many people will ask me to talk just so they can hear your Australian accent. . WHERE TO NEXT IN THE STATES . I must say in the next 5 years the states is back on my list. I'm hanging to go to Nashville and New Orlenes (I heard is the much better version of Vegas) on the list is also Chicago, Route 66, Memphis and Alabama. I think it's time to see some of the southern places.... 😁 . Have you been to America? 🇷🇺{English🔽}Наш такой спонтанный трип подошёл к концу. Сидим в аэропорту, ждём вылета домой. Эта поездка была очень интересной и не стандартной: 📚все бронирование и планирование делал муж. Я накидала ему идей и советов друзей, он обзванивал всех и все и спланировал поездку. Сказал, что устал заниматься организацией и что ценит ещё больше, когда я это делаю. 🚗Машину впервые брали в сервисе Turo- это как Airbnb для машин, то есть когда ты арендуешь машину у человека, а не у компании по аренде машин. Стоимость оказалась очень приемлемая и выбор машин тоже был получше, чем у автопрокатных фирм. 🍔Рестораны в этот раз искали на ходу, копаясь в Yelp вместо бронирования заранее. Нам понравилось, придаёт некий романтизм поездке, когда не знаешь, что дальше и где ты остановишься, чтобы перекусить. ________ А как вы любите путешествовать: на все готовое в тур, чтобы ни о чем не думать или планируете сами и на ходу меняете и адаптируетесь? 🇺🇸This awesome 3 day trip is over. 📚My hubby planned everything from scratch this time: he did all the research about Napa and wineries. The experience was amazing! I know some of you have sent us ideas-thank you for this! 🚗This time we also used Turo to rent a car and we are more than happy with the experience- it is easy, reliable and a great deal. Highly recommend! Hope you had an awesome weekend as well! ___________ #alenamerica #sanfrancisco #napavalley #alenamerica_travel #rusinusa #russianamerica #русскаядуша #русскиевсша #русскаяамерика #русскиевамерике #rusamericans

Friday we had appointments in the city. We had a couple of hours to burn, and since we were over in the Sunset, we went to the zoo since I had never been to the SF Zoo before. As a child, all through my young adult years... I have always enjoyed [loved] going to zoos and aquariums. It's a fine line... I love experiencing and learning about animals, but at the same time I also wish they were safe to freely roam in their natural habitat, without fear of being hunted or displaced. Ideally, a holographic zoo would be the best compromise. Granted, if poachers and land cultivation keep endangering the animals... we may not have a choice in that. Many of the animals we saw were on the critically endangered list. And... we just happened to go on the day that Uulu, their Polar Bear passed away, she was 36. I do wish that some of the enclosures were bigger, but it was still a nice zoo. We will, of course, continue to do our part to support and bring awareness to Ocean & Wildlife Conservation... and hopefully have an opportunity to impart that onto the next generation. We did however, have way too much fun playing on all the play structures throughout the zoo. We are definitely overgrown children. #SanFranciscoZoo #SanFrancisco #Zoo #CityZoo #ILoveAnimals #Animals #TheSunset #OliviaAndBear #IHeartMyBear

The VW will reveal their new electric crossover this week at Shanghai Motor Show. . The company released a couple of rendering teasers what is supposed to be a new electric concept crossover. . VW says that the CUV will have autonomous capabilities that will be activated by a simple push VW logo on the steering wheel. In self-driving mode, the steering wheel will be retracted into a car's dashboard. . The concept will have a high capacity battery that gives it a long range on a single charge, similar to gas powered car ranges. . The electric car will feature an all-wheel drive system as well. . The production version of the vehicle will not see the market until at least 2020. . The U.S. travel and tourism industry generated nearly $1.6 trillion in economic output in 2015, supporting 7.6 million U.S. jobs. Travel and tourism exports accounted for 11 percent of all U.S. exports and nearly a third (33 percent) of all U.S. services exports, positioning travel and tourism as the nation's largest services export. One out of every 18 Americans is employed, either directly or indirectly, in a travel or tourism-related industry. In 2015, U.S. travel and tourism output represented 2.6 percent of gross domestic product.  While the majority of activity in the industry is domestic, expenditures by international visitors in the United States totaled $246.2 billion in 2015, yielding a $97.9 billion trade surplus for the year. According to U.S. Department of Commerce projections, international travel to the United States should grow by 3 percent annually through 2021. Hello, Everyone! I hope everyone had a wonderful weekend and you’re starting off this new week with a spring in your step! I have some fantastic news I want to share with you! 🦋 This May I am taking a leap into the unknown and embarking on a journey the likes of which I have never experienced before. 🦋 I’m traveling to Peru to participate in ayahuasca ceremony. I’ll be visiting a retreat center in Iquitos and imbibing the sacred plant/vine under the supervision of several Shipibo shamans. I will be undergoing six ceremonies within ten days. 🦋 I have been dreaming of such an experience for quite some time, and when I decided to ask the Universe to show me how I might have such an experience, I received an email in my inbox inviting me to a Peruvian retreat center the next day. As I am a firm believer in synchronicity, I decided to take the leap of faith and respond. 🦋 As I wrote in my application, I am going to Peru for the transformation of my emotional, intellectual, physical and spiritual health. I seek a higher connection to the divine within and without. I wish to expand my perspective of my life’s purpose. Since I was a teenager, I have been seeking connection to spirit through the Tarot, awakening my unconsciousness on an ever unfolding path. Now that path has led me here. 🦋 I depart San Francisco for Peru on May 15th and I return June 2nd, and I am taking as many clients as I can before I leave. Please consider coming in for a reading for yourself, with a loved one (couples readings are a great way to bond, no matter what your relationship), or give a reading as a gift to a friend. I provide readings in person and over the phone. I enjoy working events and am available to bring my talents to home or office parties as well. 🦋 I also teach Tarot to individuals and groups; I’d be more than happy to schedule a workshop with a group of your friends. I am also accepting donations via PayPal (stormantic@gmail.com) and Venmo (@Storm-Arcana). If you have a low-income situation, are a student or in the military, let me know and we can make arrangements for you. 💙CONTINUED IN THE COMMENTS💙

Cобирай свою сумку, мы уезжаем. Туда, где свобода не знает границ, не знает ни денег, ни алкогольного рая, где никто не посмеет крикнуть: остановись. Собирай свою сумку, мы уезжаем. Туда, где реальность выпущена на волю из книг. Где леса пахнут хвоей, где мятное море, где звездное небо как дачное радио доносит до путников свой птичий крик. Собирай свою сумку, приятель, не медли на сопливые сантименты времени нет. Просто собирай свою сумку, садись в машину и представляй всю дорогу как самый лучший, лихо закрученный, неповторимый, очень приятный сюжет. #dream #dreams #draw #mood #mysoul #freedom #flowers #inspiration #italy #sun #smile #free #sketch #travel #traveler #france #paris #milan #sanfrancisco

This week’s topic #Break  This picture captures the essence of this week’s topic perfectly! My boy found the peace in the chaos of fishermans wharf one day.  This topic first came to mind because it’s #springbreak for our daughter but also because it’s always good to just take a break. Your mind, body, and soul all need it.  It’s proven science that when you allow your mind and body to rest and relax everything actually works better. You’re more focused, less anxious, have clearer thinking, and are overall more productive at whatever tasks you are doing. Who doesn’t need that in this busy busy life?  So this week I want to talk, share, receive, all ideas, tips, things related to taking a break. I’ve got LOTS to share but want to know What that means for you? How I do it? How you do it? AND how the universe plays its hand in it. . . . #mind #body #soul #selfcare #selflove #clarity #focus #mondaymotivation #monday #momlife #motherhood #lifeisbusy #lifeiscrazy #life #productivity #myboy #son #beach #sanfrancisco #ghirardelli #bay #fishermanswharf #wellwmn #citybythebay #angelisland #pirateships #balance

Ginger Shrimp and Mango Skewers with Paleo Crema  _______________________________________________________  All who know me know that I absolutely LOVE shrimp! 💜 🍤 This is why I'm super excited to share a recipe that combines two of my favorite things... shrimp and essential oils!! Lemon and Ginger essential oils give just the right something to push this already marvelous recipe to star status. 💫 Bon appétit! 👩‍🍳🙌 _______________________________________________________  Marinade: ■ 1 pound shrimp, raw, peeled and deveined with tails cut off ■ 2 tablespoons olive oil ■ 1/2-1 tsp crushed red pepper flakes ■ 1 full lemon's worth of zest ■ 2 large cloves garlic ■ 1 drop Ginger essential oil ■ 3 drops Lemon essential oil ■ 3 heaping tablespoons fresh, chopped cilantro ■ Sea salt and freshly ground pepper to taste  _______________________________________________________  For the Skewers: ■ 2 mangoes ■ Wooden skewers, soaked for at least an hour before grilling so they don't burn  _______________________________________________________ For the Crema: ■ Half a tin of full-fat coconut milk (if you have coconut cream that works great too!) ■ All of the juice from the zested lemon ■ 2 drops Lemon essential oil ■ Salt and pepper to taste ■ 3 heaping tablespoons fresh, chopped cilantro  _______________________________________________________ Instructions: ■ Start with the shrimp. Put all ingredients for Shrimp marinade into a gallon-sized plastic bag and shake mixture until evenly coated. Leave shrimp to marinate for 1-24 hours. ■ Begin marinating skewers at least one hour in advance of grilling. ■ The crema can be made hours in advance or right before grilling. Put all of the crema ingredients in a medium bowl and whisk to combine. ■ Before you are ready to begin grilling, cut mangoes into chunks and thread the skewers, alternating shrimp and mango. ■ On a hot grill, cook the skewers for 2-3 minutes per side, leaving the skewer alone until you flip it so you can get those gorgeous grill marks. The most common way to to ruin shrimp is to overcook it. Watch it carefully. ■ Put skewers on a serving platter, drizzle with loads of crema and cilantro

Almeno in parte, tralasciando i dettagli inaspettati e le coincidenze 😏, avevamo previsto un disastro del genere 😂..ma di quelli positivi eh😏.. partendo in ritardo per la sveglia impostata male (avendo dormito solo 4 ore) vivendo un viaggio di andata di 5 ore di risate assurde 😅, proseguendo con lo scambiarsi le camere, (senza sapere ancora adesso il perché) con l'incontro assurdo del nostro amico 'Francesco Arca' 😱..(mini infarto gratuito)passando per il centro sconosciuto (solo per pochi minuti) di Mi.Ma, tra chi ci riconosceva e chi ci salutava urlando in bicicletta 😂.. arrivando in spiaggia dove abbiamo dato subito prova del nostro modo di essere sgarruppate,(anche scappando in mezzo alla gente coraggiosa, che prendeva il sole e faceva il bagno con 12 gradi 🤔).. e camminando all'inifinito, quasi del tutto a caso, per raggiungere la nostra meta.. (che per quei cattivi seguaci che non se ne fossero accorti, era il Papeete)😎 dalla quale non solo ci siamo fatte riconoscere in tempo record, ma abbiamo dato il via a una situazione infinita, di assoluto e fantastico degenero, che difficilmente dimenticheremo 😏🔝.. soprattutto per i follower e le loro dirette/le foto dai tetti/gli adesivi sulla pancia/le foto/ancora foto/i continui innamoramenti lampo/le corse a caso tra le sdraio/trovarsi a saltare sotto i gazebi/gli incontri del tutto casuali 😂/lo sputtanamento totale nelle ig stories/i bicchieri che cambiavano colore/le tante, tantissime figure di merda divertenti/le troppe risate e gli abbracci vari con tutti/il sorriso perenne/altre foto senza senso/i braccialettiiii 😍/ il freddo porco/il buio all'improvviso (ancora non capisco come abbia fatto a passare così velocemente dal giorno alla notte.. ed infine perderci senza sapere come, quando e perché 🙈.. ma dopo tutta questa recensione generale possiamo confermare di aver dato a quel posto e a quella gente il meglio e il peggio 😂..di noi stesse😇. Missions and Outreach are one of the 4 core values here at Salem Alliance. At the end of March, we commissioned a student team for San Francisco with plans to spend time serving the poor, processing food bank donations and assembling lunches for delivery.  If you can believe it, our amazing team of 8th graders were able to sort through tens of thousands of apples 🍎 at the food bank and were able to deliver way more lunches than anticipated which lead to assembling their own lunches from scratch so they could continue to serve and reach more members of that community.  The students were definitely changed as well and were delighted to share their stories. Some quotes about the trip from our students: "Had an amazing time serving the homeless community and spreading God's light to them." "This truly was the best week of my life! I became closer to God as I was serving the homeless. We went there to spread the word of God, but it was really impacting for us both." "Life changing" "life changing" and "life changing"  #salemalliance #worldimpact#studentministries #serve #outreach#sanfrancisco #missiontripmonday#latergram

TAFC.2017.36 Knights Templars Passing Palace Hotel—President McKinley’s Visit. San Francisco, Cal, U.S.A. 1901 3.5 x 7  Maker: Keystone View Company  Stereoview or stereocard made by Keystone View Company. View down Market Street, showing the Palace Hotel (the highest building in view), a parade passing. Both sides of the street are packed with onlookers, three streetcars visible on their tracks, and several ranks of Knights Templar are visible parading toward the camera. A large flag flies over the hotel. Lines or wires over and across the street seem to  be festooned with greenery. In foreground is visible a car with the word MODER emblazoned across its side.  Dark tan card mount (older Keystone color). Bottom edge caption: “12400—Knights Templars Passing Palace Hotel—President McKinley’s Visit, San Francisco, Cal, U.S.A.” Along dexter edge: “Keystone View Company, Manufacturers and Publishers” Along sinister edge: “Meadville, Pa.  St Louis, Mo.  Copyright 1901 by B.L. Singley”  Condition: good. Card edges are gently worn overall. LL corner is a bit bumped at verso edge. Card mount is two layers laminated, and are delaminated at all corners except UR, delamination extends along the edges, especially UL. Mount is very grubby, evenly, overall. 9/100 #100daysofpatterninspirationbycata ✨ Today I am honoring a few of my favorite artists that have passed on who are huge creative influences (and pattern inspirers!) in my life. I discovered Rex Ray while living in San Francisco- the fabulous @jonathanadler on Filmore carried his originals and I would visit them often. I remember excitedly finding out that his studio was just a few blocks away from mine in the Mission, I thought about writing him to visit his studio and then had a moment of shyness 🙈 and never did. I wish I would have because he passed away in 2015 after quietly battling lymphoma. His work lives on and I am hugely inspired ever time I see it. He is one of my mentors too in the dual place he kept in both the fine art/museum world and the licensing/design world- he created album covers, scarves, rugs, even car wraps for Smart cars! I believe that the more places we can put art, live with art, the better off we are. Thank you Rex Ray!! 💕

"My argument against God was that the universe seemed so cruel and unjust. But how had I gotten this idea of just and unjust? A man does not call a line crooked unless he has some idea of a straight line. What was I comparing this universe with when I called it unjust? If the whole show was bad and senseless from A to Z, so to speak, why did I, who was supposed to be part of the show, find myself in such violent reaction against it? A man feels wet when he falls into water, because man is not a water animal: a fish would not feel wet. Of course I could have given up my idea of justice by saying it was nothing but a private idea of my own. But if I did that, then my argument against God collapsed too — for the argument depended on saying that the world was really unjust." - C. S. Wowzers! I've been working on a #mindmap for the #matsbootcamp2017 assignment. I got really into this.  It tells my story of living in #sanfrancisco the past 10 years and the #leapsoffaith I've taken along the way. The first leap of faith was moving up here with only an apartment lined up in 2007. Fast forward to 2013, another leap of faith was leaving corporate America to pursue art. I had no idea what that looked like at the time, nor had I sold any of my art before. Fast forward another three years, this summer, I celebrate three years of 100% self-employment making and selling my art in San Francisco. As the mind map suggests, sometimes there's not a clear path outlined, but as long as I follow my joy, I'm confident that I'll find my way. #sanfrancisco #artist #followyourjoy #guidance #lighhouse #sailboats #collage #wallpaper

В выходные мы ездили в замечательные места близ Сан-Франциско🔅⠀ Давайте разберемся с точки зрения туриста, где интересней: в Южной или Северной части Калифорнии?⠀ ⠀ 🔹Американские горки и парки развлечений (такие как Sea World, Safari Zoo, #Zoo, #Legoland, #DisneyLand, Knotts Berry Farm, Six Flags, #Universal) сосредоточены в Южной части (район Лос-Анджелеса и Сан-Диего);⠀ 🔹Погода. В южной части очень жарко летом (до +40), зимой - 15-25. В Сан-Франциско прохладнее и ветренее🌬⠀ 🔹Общественный транспорт в южной части не развит, можно сказать😬 Необходимо брать машину в аренду🚙 #СФ компактней и общественный транспорт развит гораздо лучше;⠀ 🔹Сан-Франциско на порядок красивее чем Лос-Анджелес и Сан-Диего, но это мое личное мнение😉 Я очень люблю дома викторианской эпохи в СФ;⠀ 🔹Природа. В окрестностях СФ явно зеленее🌳 #Океан, пляжи есть по всему побережью Калифорнии. Но в северной части эти места живописней😍⠀ ⠀ Так что общего ответа на мой вопрос нет😅 Смотря что вам интересно. Если это парки развлечений🎢🎡, то вам однозначно в Южную часть.⠀ ⠀ А лучше всего взять машину и прокатиться вдоль побережья🌊, погулять по Санта-Барбаре, заехать в Датский городок Солванг,  побывать в национальных парках волшебной красоты - Sequoia National Park и Yosemite National Park. Погулять по сказочному городу Кармел и морскому городу Монтерей. Прокатиться по Биг-Сюр и сделать невероятные снимки океана и гор🏔🌊. В СФ покататься на трамвайчиках, погулять по холмам и накачать себе попу как орех🌰😀 Взять велосипеды в аренду и колесить по городу🚲, любуясь и разглядывая все красоты👀💙⠀ ⠀ А куда поехали бы вы? Какой город больше на слуху? И что для вас в приоритете при выборе путешествий? ⠀ ⠀ Хорошего дня 🙌🏻⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ 🌎Девочки, кто участвовал в #кругосветказа7дней, проверьте ваши подписки 😉 результаты будут в среду! 😎
